result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

8:33 AM Defendant Brittany Simone Rabbitt in court, in custody.  Attorney Mark Adam Fruehauf in court for State of Wisconsin. Court callse case and indicates Attorney Gramstrup withdrew on March 13th.  Ms. Rabbitt planning on representing herself today but will attempt to get a lawyer. Defendant reads letter to court regarding bail modification. Asks to the court to revise bail so she can enter treatment at Farmin Treatment Center once a bed become available. 
State is opposed. Has 3 other files here with $8,000 posted between them, those files include bail jumping. Lengthy prior history with many FTA's. Cites prior convictions. 21cf437 FTA on 2000 cash, in October 2021, did not return until November. The prior bail modification was for her to go to Farmin Treatment Center and she did not go. Believes current bail more than appropriate. 
Defendant states ride she had failed through but she has a ride now.
Court makes statements. Not convinced she will show up to treatment.  Request for bail modification denied.

01:39 PM Defendant Brittany Simone Rabbitt in court with attorney Michael Charles Hoffman who makes Special Appearance as Mr. Gramstrap is not available. Defendant Brittany Simone Rabbitt in custody.  Mark Adam Fruehauf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Brittany Simone Rabbitt appeared by video means with Attorney Hoffman. Defendant gives current address. Court indicates the warrant was filed as a Motion by the State and will quash the warrant. Court questions atty Hoffman regarding moving forward on the Motion by the State. Atty Hoffman indicates he is willing to move forward as long as Defendant wants to move forward on the State's Motion. Defendant asserts she is willing to move forward. State indicates a written Motion was filed and outlines the basis for the request. State asserts there was a Status Conference held on Monday, February 28th.  Prior to that Status, this Court ordered cash bail to be released in this matter. Defense Counsel was able to get defendant into Farmham treatment center and stay there until her release. State , Defense Counsel, and Attorney Gramstrup did enter into a Stipulation on Monday and was approved by Judge Glonek on the same day. Judge Glonek did grant the modification of cash bond to a signature bond and the condition of her bail was to immediately go to the Treatment Center and remain there till her release. State indicates that he verified Defendant did not appear at the treatment center. Therefore, asking Judge Glonek to issue the warrant without a hearing. Judge Glonek did issue the warrant. State asks for increase in bail and that the original $10,000 should be put back in place. State requests conditions to be no violent or abusive contact with Jeffrey Rabbitt and to remove the special condition of reporting to the treatment center. 
Atty Hoffman offers his advice of Defendant to remain silent until she is able to speak directly with her counsel. Atty Hoffman argues bail on behalf of defendant. Defendant can post up to $1000.
Court has concerns with the allegations and continued behaviour of not following Court Orders. Court will reinstate the cash bail of $10,000 with conditions of no violent or abusive contact with Jeffery Rabbitt.  Status conference scheduled for May 2, 2022 at 09:00 am.
